init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: She usually never let you outside or out of her sight, but today was out of town. She had locked the bedroom door, but being a clever girl, you knew how to get out, into the forbidden outdoors.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She usually never let you outside or out of her sight, but today was out of town. She had locked the bedroom door, but being a clever girl, you knew how to get out, into the forbidden outdoors.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" it asks again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not the queen," you say, "I'm just a girl."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You are the queen, my Queen," the bee says, "and I am your loyal servant.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "My mother is fine," you say, "I just saw her."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "They have taken over your mother's body and mind."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "But I can't leave," you say, "I'm allergic to bees."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: a lie your mother has told you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "She is a wasp, and she has lied to you all your life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I will give you time," the bee says, "but remember, you are the queen.
